comment:
DC is confused. The producers are having trouble with their demographic. They want to make their movies (best example is Wonder Woman) like Marvel has been but that just won't work. They're characters don't fit in a fantastic setting. Their style has always been gritty. The movie series will continue to fail if they don't own their darker roots.

There have been movies that double down on this darker tone. But on my life every time they blur the line between good and evil they turn the movie into a fight scene. They need: Hard moral decisions; blurry lines between right and wrong; and more conversations and downtime between fighting to let the morals of everything sink in. 

Best DC movies of all time are the dark night and watchmen. The watchmen isn't all it could have been but what they did right was let that gritty DC vibe run rampant.

I trust Snyder, if anyone can do it I believe he can but he needs full control. I see the image of the joker as a good sign that he wants to blur the line between good and evil. So until further notice I'm giving this a shot.
